      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * William Uther</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:218px;\"><a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=-qvphmUAAAAJ\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/b/bc/WTBUther.jpg\" width=\"216\" height=\"256\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:WTBUther.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>William Uther <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>William T. B. Uther</b>,<br />\nan Australian computer scientist at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NICTA\">NICTA</a> and School of Computer Science and Engineering, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_New_South_Wales\">University of New South Wales</a> (UNSW) with research interests in <a href=\"/Reinforcement_Learning\" title=\"Reinforcement Learning\">Reinforcement Learning</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soccer_robot\">Robot Soccer</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Driverless_car\">Autonomous Driving</a>.  He defended his Ph.D in Computer Science at <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a> in 2002 <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1997_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1997 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1997_...\">1997 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1997 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a>, <a href=\"/Manuela_Veloso\" title=\"Manuela Veloso\">Manuela M. Veloso</a> (<b>1997</b>). <i>Adversarial Reinforcement Learning</i>. <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a>, <a href=\"/Manuela_Veloso\" title=\"Manuela Veloso\">Manuela M. Veloso</a> (<b>1997</b>). <i>Generalizing Adversarial Reinforcement Learning</i>. <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a> (<b>2002</b>). <i>Tree Based Hierarchical Reinforcement Learning</i>. Ph.D thesis, <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://reports-archive.adm.cs.cmu.edu/anon/2002/CMU-CS-02-169.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Kee_Siong_Ng&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Kee Siong Ng (page does not exist)\">Kee Siong Ng</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Lloyd&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"John Lloyd (page does not exist)\">John Lloyd</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Probabilistic modelling, inference and learning using logical theories</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://users.cecs.anu.edu.au/~kee/prihol.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Joel_Veness\" title=\"Joel Veness\">Joel Veness</a>, <a href=\"/David_Silver\" title=\"David Silver\">David Silver</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a>, <a href=\"/Alan_Blair\" title=\"Alan Blair\">Alan Blair</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://papers.nips.cc/paper/3722-bootstrapping-from-game-tree-search\">Bootstrapping from Game Tree Search</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://jveness.info/publications/nips2009%20-%20bootstrapping%20from%20game%20tree%20search.pdf\">pdf</a> </li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Joel_Veness\" title=\"Joel Veness\">Joel Veness</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Kee_Siong_Ng&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Kee Siong Ng (page does not exist)\">Kee Siong Ng</a>, <a href=\"/Marcus_Hutter\" title=\"Marcus Hutter\">Marcus Hutter</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a> , <a href=\"/David_Silver\" title=\"David Silver\">David Silver</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i>A Monte-Carlo AIXI Approximation</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">JAIR</a>, Vol. 40, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.aaai.org/Papers/JAIR/Vol40/JAIR-4004.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/referenceworkentry/10.1007/978-1-4899-7687-1_512\">Markov Decision Processes</a></i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Claude_Sammut\">Claude Sammut</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geoff_Webb\">Geoffrey I. Webb</a> (eds) (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/referencework/10.1007%2F978-1-4899-7687-1\">Encyclopedia of Machine Learning and Data Mining</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media\">Springer</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">William Uther</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/referenceworkentry/10.1007/978-1-4899-7687-1_817\">Temporal Difference Learning</a></i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Claude_Sammut\">Claude Sammut</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geoff_Webb\">Geoffrey I. Webb</a> (eds) (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/referencework/10.1007%2F978-1-4899-7687-1\">Encyclopedia of Machine Learning and Data Mining</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media\">Springer</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=-qvphmUAAAAJ\">William T. B. Uther - Google Scholar Citations</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://plus.google.com/117333205909949323908\">William Uther - Google+</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=William_Uther&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&amp;user=-qvphmUAAAAJ\">William T. B. Uther - Google Scholar Citations<